Prompt for literature review
Write a critical and analytical literature review of 1000 to 1200 words on [insert your topic here], directly related to the clear objectives of the study [ also insert the objectives of the study]. To begin, provide a comprehensive overview and explanation of the topic, including its significance. Then, critically synthesise the most relevant literature to your research aims. Examine how each study critically considers its aim, method, findings, and limitations. Point out how each study contributes to the research problem. Use the comparison of results to identify patterns, contradictions, and knowledge gaps. Finally, assess the overall quality of the literature, whether it aligns with the study's aims and objectives, and how your research will address the gap. Make sure the answer is written in formal academic style, fit for a {standard of a journal} journal, with a logical flow and proper citations using APA 7th edition where relevant.
